 in the analysis of travel demand patterns.  I have designed a number of the components of the Department for Transport’s National Transport </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">Model that </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">DfT have used to </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">develop the forecasts of SRN traffic.  I have a long-term personal interest in ensuring that transport planning policy takes appropriate account of the influence</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> f</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">rom</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> land-use planning policy and vice-versa</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> so that the adminis</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">trative separation between DCLG and DfT does not hamper </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">effective policy decisions.</span></h3><h3 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">1.1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">This response focuses primarily on </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">the issue</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span></h3><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">How reliable is the Government’s forecast for growth in demand for the strategic road network? How should the Government dea</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">l with uncertainty in its forecast?</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">” </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">How does the Government’s policy for roads link with planning for other transport modes?</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">”</span></li></ul><h2 style="font-size:14pt; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><a name="_Toc369688654"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">Executive</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-wei