0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">Research </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">int</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">o the impacts of PPG13 </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">and related planning policies</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">that </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">acted </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">from the 1990s </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">until recently</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">to encourage urban densification</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">ha</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> indicated that </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">these policies </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">ha</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">played a substantial part in lowering the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">high </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">rate of growth in car travel demand</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> seen in previous decades</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">  There is no guarantee that the urban densification trends that emerged over the last 10-15 years will continue to occur </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">as an outcome from</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> the changed </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">land-use </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">planning system </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">in operation</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> today</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> Accordingly, </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">the implications of this uncertainty over future residential and employment location trends should be considered explicitly</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> in the scenarios on future traffic growth</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">  Otherwise, the</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">se</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> forecasts</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> could be quite misleading.</span></h3><h3 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">1.2.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">The</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">se</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> policies of urban densification have also acted </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">indirectly</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> to promote rail growth, both for commuting and for </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">inter-urban </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">travel</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">.  They have</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> increas</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">ed </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">the size of market in central city areas where cars are expen</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">sive to use and </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">are </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">subject to substantial congestion in the peaks.</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> In this way these policies </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">have been a major </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">contributor</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">the rapid recent growth in rail passenger travel, which contrasts </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">with the</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> much slower recent growth in car travel.</span></h3><h3 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">1.2.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">backgro</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">und</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">evidence </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">underlying</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> th</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">statements </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">summarised </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">in the following sections.</span></h3><h2 style="font-size:14pt; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><a name="_Toc369688655"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">Model </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">F</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">orm</span></a><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold"> </span></h2><h3 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">1.3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">To address the aims of this consultation, this section focusses on those few aspects of the forecasting tools of DfT that need to be improved, and does not discus</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">s the much larger set of aspects which already function well</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> within the National Transport Model (NTM)</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">.</span></h3><h3 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">1.3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">The form of the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">NTM </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">that was used for the road traffic forecasts is outlined in p.4 of “</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">Road Transport Forecasts 2013</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">”, which lists the five travel choi</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">ce dimensions that govern the operation of the model.  Although, these include a dimension of choice of destination of travel, there is no explicit representation that the origin </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">(within the NTM th</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">origin</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">”</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> mainly denotes the residential location of the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">traveller) </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">might differ between scenarios or as a result of government policies.  </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">This assum</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">ption of</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">certainty </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">and of stability across policies </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">in future location patterns is important for reasons now explained.</span></h3><h3 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">1.3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">The assumptions on population location and growth patterns used for these traffic forecasts were based on the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">ONS 2008 Principle Population projections</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">The meta-data for these projections state explicitly “</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">The projections do not take into account any fut</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">ure policy changes that have not yet occurred</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">”.  </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">In principle, this would appear to suggest that the effects of </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">densification policies </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">already </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">in operation </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25p