hoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">which is </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">due to </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> strong densification</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> there</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> has been 50</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">+</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">% higher than </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">that observed in the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">South East (0.8%) and South West (0.7%)</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">.  This indicates that spatial impac</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">ts of the policy of densification </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">appear not to </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">have been captured within the population projections </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">underpinning </span><span style="font-family:'Cen