g:0.25pt">the future </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">growth rates</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> which</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> are due to local circumstances rather than </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">simply </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">global </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">income or car </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">purchasing</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> cost changes.  In particular, it </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> not </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">clear whether it has </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">fore</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">cast the major reductions in car ownership rates that have been observed </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">since 2001 </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">in many</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> fast-growing</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> dense urban areas.</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">  </span></h3><h2 style="font-size:14pt; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><a name="_Toc369688656"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">Analysis of Residential Location and Travel Demand</span></a></h2><h3 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">1.4.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">Recent research at Cambridge University has analysed the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">impacts of urban </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">densification on the s</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">upply and demand for transport (Williams &amp; Jin, 2013</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">).  This has used Census data f</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">r</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">om</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> 1981 to 2011, plus data from the National Travel Survey to analyse how longer</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">term changes in land-use patterns have impacted on trends in travel d</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">emand by mode.  The main findings relevant to this Inquiry </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">are now summarised</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">. </span></h3><h3 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">1.4.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">Within many of the economically dynamic larger cities that </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">recently </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">have been growing rapidly and increasing in urban density, m</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">any of the long running travel demand trends tha</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">t had been the norm since the 70s have either slowed down or reversed </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">over</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> the last decade.  </span></h3><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">Back in the 1980s, car ownership rates, car usage and average annual distance travelled per capita, all tended to increase at broadly similar rates (though often </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">from different base positions) across area types ranging from the most rural to the highest density urban.  This spatial consistency in behaviour is no longer observed in the most recent decade 2001-11.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">For Inner London residents, between 2001 and 2011 </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> mode share of </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">commuting by car has reduced by 7 percentage points, with this </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">share</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> switching to cycle (+3</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">%</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">age</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> points)</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> to bus (+2</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> %age</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> points) and </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">rail (+2</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> %age </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">points)</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">.  Despite </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">the major</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> increase of </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">465,000</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">+</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">1</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">7</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">%)</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> in </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">its</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> resident population</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">, the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">tot</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">al </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">number of cars available to </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">Inner London </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">residents actually reduced by 26,000 </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">   </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">(-4%).</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">  Car ownership rates per adult in Inner London have </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">now </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">returned </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">back </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">down to the rates last seen in </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">1981</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> Census</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">In contrast, t</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">he most </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">rural areas, </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">despite alre</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">ady having the highest car ownership rates </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">per adult </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">in </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">England in </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">2001, </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">still </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">experienced the greatest rate </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">of increase in car ownership rates through to 2011.</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> There is no convincing evidence there of a saturation level being reached in car ownership rat</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">es.</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">However, </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">Inner London and other dense conurbation centres, which </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">already </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">in 2001 had the lowest car ownership rates</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> in England</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">, experienced significant reductions in these rates through to 2011.</span></li></ul><h3 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">1.4.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">is and other related </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">evidence demonstrates that </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">volume of traffic currently observed on the SRN would have been very much greater now, if there had not been a major policy driven switch over the last 15 years to bring about urban densification in the spatial patterns of residential and employment growth</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">  It is not evident that the NTM as it is currently constructed takes full account of these important behavioural trends when developing its future traffic forecasts.</span></h3><h2 style="font-size:14pt; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt 28.8pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-28.8pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">1.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><a name="_Toc369688657"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold">PPG13 Study by WSP</span></a><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:14pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold"> </span></h2><h3 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">1.5.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> past modelling study has endeavoured to estimate the scale of </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">reduction in road travel demand aris</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> from </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> policy of urban densification of residential and employment patterns.  This forecasting was carried out by WSP plus Arup within a major study</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">for DfT </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">(WSP &amp; Arup, 2005)</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">It investigated </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">travel demand </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">im</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">pacts of the PPG13 planning policy, which then was the main policy promoting urban densification.  It carried out </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">scenario tests</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> using the LASER (London And South East Region) integrated land use and transport model to measure and analyse </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">between 1998 and </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">2016 </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">the impacts on travel demand of three scenarios: a continuation of the current guidance framework </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">(e.g. PPG13) </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">versus loosening </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">(e.g. a return to the 80s) </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">or strengthening the policy criteria (e.g. </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">greater</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> densification</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> plus widespread road pricing</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">). </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span></h3><h3 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">1.5.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">scenario testing </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">results</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> included:</span></h3><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">The LASER model shows that </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">impact on morning peak travel of loosening the</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">land use policy guidance would be a rise in car passenger-km by 4% by 2016 in the</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">South East and East of England, over and above the lev</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">el under Current Policy. </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">… This suggests that the rise in the car passenger-km would be between 3-4% over the Current Policy Scenario, which is equivalent to 15-20% of the total forecast growth in car passenger-km for the period 1997/98 to 2016.” (page 56,</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> WSP</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt"> &amp; Arup</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt">, 2005)</span></p><h3 style="font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal; line-height:113%; margin:10pt 0pt 0pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">1.5.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">Th</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> model run</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">, although it is now somewhat dated,</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">illustrates</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">scale of the </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">road traffic growth impact </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">that would arise should the current </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">land-use </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">planning system lead to a </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">rever</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">sal back </span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">to the 80s p</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt">attern of dispersal of employment</span><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:11pt; letter-spacing:0.25pt"> and residential growth. </span></h3><h1 style="font-size:16pt; line-height:115%; margin:24pt 0pt 0pt 21.6pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:16pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt">2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><a name="_Toc369688658"><span style="font-family:'Century Schoolbook'; font-size:16pt; font-variant:small-caps; font-weight:bold; letter-spacing:0.25pt">References</span></a></h1><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:'